summary: A U.S. Customs and Border Protection TECS Person Encounter List detailing 58 international travel entries for Ghislaine Maxwell between 1990 and 1999. The document shows her frequent travel between the United States (primarily New York, Miami, Los Angeles) and Europe (primarily London and Paris).

keyFacts: The document is a law enforcement sensitive travel log generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on January 16, 2020.
It records 58 separate international travel events for Ghislaine Maxwell between December 1990 and December 1999.
Travel was frequent and primarily between major U.S. hubs (JFK, MIA, LAX) and European hubs (LHR, CDG).
The document shows Maxwell used both a passport (P) and an Alien Registration Card (A) for travel.
The data was likely compiled as part of an investigation, evidenced by the SDNY (Southern District of New York) file reference numbers.
